					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Portability is great, but how many people that are all about it actually make sure their code runs on all of Windows, *nix, and Mac? Nevermind the fact that newer Macs make it so they don't have to care about non-x86 platforms.
<br />
<br />I have noticed lately that I need to use long long to get 64bit "u64" typedefs on both i586 and x86-64 gcc, so I really shouldn't talk.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" />  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_cool.gif" alt="8)" title="Cool" /></div>

